    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>White, crystalline compound formerly used extensively as wood preservative, antiseptic and disinfectant, insecticide, and, in archival conservation, a fungicide for paper and books. Due to its toxicity mercuric chloride's use is now restricted in the U.S.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
